  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I change the nominee details in Atal Pension Yojana?",
  "response": "Yes, you can **change the nominee details** in the **Atal Pension Yojana (APY)**. Updating your nominee is an important step to ensure that your pension benefits are smoothly transferred to your chosen beneficiary in the event of your demise. Here's how you can make the change:\n\n### **Steps to Change Nominee Details in APY:**\n\n1. **Contact Your Service Provider:**\n   - APY is typically managed through various service providers such as **banks**, **post offices**, or **insurance companies**. Reach out to the institution where you initially enrolled in the APY.\n\n2. **Obtain the Nomination Change Form:**\n   - Request a **nomination change form** from your service provider. Some institutions may also provide this form online through their official websites or mobile applications.\n\n3. **Fill Out the Form:**\n   - Complete the form with the required details, including:\n     - **Existing Nominee Details:** Information about the current nominee.\n     - **New Nominee Details:** Full name, relationship, date of birth, and other relevant information of the new nominee.\n     - **Policy Details:** Your APY account number and other necessary identification details.\n\n4. **Submit Required Documents:**\n   - Provide **proof of identity** and **address** for both yourself and the new nominee. Commonly accepted documents include:\n     - **Aadhar Card**\n     - **Passport**\n     - **Voter ID**\n     - **PAN Card**\n   - Some service providers may require **recent photographs** of the new nominee.\n\n5. **Verification Process:**\n   - The service provider will review the submitted form and documents. This may involve verifying the details provided to ensure accuracy.\n\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - Once your request is processed, you will receive a **confirmation receipt** or **updated policy document** indicating the change in nominee details.\n\n### **Additional Considerations:**\n\n- **Timelines:** The processing time for nominee changes can vary between service providers. It's advisable to inquire about the expected timeframe when submitting your request.\n  \n- **Multiple Nominees:** APY allows you to nominate **more than one person** as beneficiaries. Ensure you specify the percentage of the pension each nominee will receive.\n\n- **Updating Beneficiaries:** It's a good practice to periodically review and update your nominee details, especially after major life events such as marriage, birth of a child, or the passing of a nominee.\n\n- **Assistance:** If you're unsure about the process, visit the nearest branch of your service provider or contact their customer service for guidance.\n\n### **Online Updates:**\n\nSome banks and service providers offer the facility to update nominee details **online** through their official websites or mobile applications. Check if this option is available with your provider for a more convenient and quicker update process.\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n\n- **Eligibility:** Only the **subscriber** of the APY can request a change in nominee details.\n  \n- **No Restrictions on Frequency:** You can change the nominee as many times as needed, provided you follow the required procedures.\n\nBy ensuring that your nominee details are up-to-date, you safeguard your loved ones' financial future through the Atal Pension Yojana.\n\nIf you encounter any difficulties or have specific queries related to your APY account, it's recommended to **contact your service provider directly** for personalized assistance.",
